{"questionId":"11820","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate the solution to a coupled system of differential equations and how to transform it to a system that can be solved by the eigenvector method.</p>\n<p>It is desired to solve the coupled system of differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = x + 2y - 50\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>50</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y = 2x + y - 40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>40</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;represent the population of two types of symbiotic coral and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is time measured in decades.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Extend this method to conjecture the limit of the ratio&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{y}{x}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\to \\infty \">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>By extending the table, conjecture that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mathop {{\\text{lim}}}\\limits_{t \\to \\infty } \\frac{y}{x} = 1\">\n  <munder>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>lim</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </munder>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11820","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Extend this method to conjecture the limit of the ratio y x as t → ∞ .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}